        <div class="description">Native perennial to eastern North America including Virginia's Piedmont. This drought-tolerant wildflower grows 1-3 feet tall with finely divided, thread-like leaves and bright yellow daisy flowers from summer through fall. Forms spreading clumps. Deadheading encourages continued blooming. Attracts butterflies and beneficial insects. Self-seeds moderately in suitable conditions.</div>
